<item>
            <title>[SPR-2271] ApplicationContext getApplicationContext() lost public access</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2271</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;All versions of Spring up to 2.0 RC1 have ApplicationContext getApplicationContext() as public scope. Suddenly it has protected scope in RC2. This breaks backwards compatibility &amp;#8211; and my code &amp;#8211; and there is no explanation for this change. Is there a good reason behind this? It is not at all compatible with 1.x code or &amp;lt; 2.0 RC2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="14486">SPR-2271</key>
            <summary>ApplicationContext getApplicationContext() lost public access</summary>
